ile (2 min., 30 sec.)) :bsound, color.  atwo-dimensional moving imagebtdi2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier0 aMinute out in it  aThis is a publication issued by the United States federal government or produced with federal funds.  aIn scope of the U.S. Government Publishing Office Cataloging and Indexing Program (C&I) and Federal Depository Library Program (FDLP).0 aConnor Chee.  aConnor Chee is a Diné pianist, who composes music inspired by his Diné heritage. "The original Diné songs I set to the piano were corn grinding songs, or girls' dance songs. But I soon began to incorporate Diné philosophy into my compositions, such as the number 4, which is sacred in Diné culture. So, whether that's through 4-part repetition, or even in the harmony, I try to imbue my music with references to 4." Spend a Minute Out In it with Connor as he performs his music for visitors in the Land of Song.  aClosed captions and audio description in English.  aDescription based on online resource; title from title screen (NPS, viewed Mar. 30, 2026).10aChee, Connor. 0aNavajo IndiansxMusic. 0aPianistszArizona. 0aComposerszArizona. 0aGrand Canyon National Park (Ariz.) 7aBiographical films.2lcgft 7aMusical films.2lcgft 7aInternet videos.2lcgft1 aChee, Connor,ecomposer,eperformer.1https://id.oclc.org/worldcat/entity/E39PCjH4rHF9f6PpKK4qqfBv6q2 aGrand Canyon National Park (Agency : U.S.),eissuing body.40uhttps://purl.fdlp.gov/GPO/gpo254518704 zAddress at time of PURL creationuhttps://www.nps.gov/media/video/view.htm?id=CB81CBA4-6F0D-4B41-AC5A-D307BA0605CC  aC0bGPO  abc109 20260422b20260422  aBIBCONEWb2026042202817ngm a2200541 i 00147151820260422155057.0m     o  c f      260422s2026    dcu103       fo   mleng c  a(OCoLC)1586876712  aGPObengerdaepncGPO  aengpengqeng  apcc  an-us-vaan-us-dc  aXZL4  a0648-A-53 (online)0 aI 29.176:G 2900aGWMP - vista management plan/env