nse for Intelligence and Security, U.S. Department of Defense; David Cattler, Director, Defense Counterintelligence and Security Agency; Radha Iyengar Plumb, Ph.D., Chief Digital and Artificial Intelligence Officer, U.S. Department of Defense; Stacey A. Dixon, Ph.D., Principal Deputy Director, Office of the Director of National Intelligence.  aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (GovInfo, viewed April 23, 2026). 0aIntelligence servicezUnited StatesxEvaluation. 0aIntelligence servicexPersonnel management. 0aSecurity clearanceszUnited States. 0aNational securityzUnited States. 7aGovernment Operations and Politics.2cgpa 7aArmed Forces and National Security.2cgpa 7aLegislative hearings.2lcgft08iPrint version:aUnited States. Congress. Senate. Select Committee on Intelligence.sOpen hearing (2024 July 10)w(OCoLC)15869204791 aUnited States.bCongress.bSenate.tS. hrg. ;v118-431.40uhttps://purl.fdlp.gov/GPO/gpo255223704 zAddress at time of PURL creationuhttps://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/CHRG-118shrg57024/pdf/CHRG-118shrg57024.pdf  aC0bGPO  abca29 20260423b20260423  aBIBCONEWb20260423  aPUBPOLTERMSb2026042302739ngm a22004453i 00147154620260423094834.0m     o  c f      260423s2025    ksu027       fo   vleng d  a(OCoLC)1586920396  aGPObengerdaepncGPO  aengpeng  ae-it---  aXZL4  a0359-C-11 (online)0 aD 110.2:W 9604aThe fight for hill 66 /ca production of Army University Films ; directed by: Roy C. Parker ; produced by: Randy G. Masten.1 iTitle from website:aWWII Italy :bbattle for hill 66. 1aFort Leavenworth, KS :bArmy University Films,c2025.  a1 online resource (1 video file (26 min., 31 sec.)) :bsound, color  atwo-dimensional moving imagebtdi2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aThis is a publication issued by the United States federal government or produced with federal funds.  aIn scope of the U.S. Government Publishing Office Cataloging and Indexing Program (C&I) and Federal Depository Library Program (FDLP).  aEdited by: Nick Schale ; assistant editor: Sara Carlsen.  aWhen viewing films on the Second World War, tactical level fights are often overlooked in favor of sweeping narratives focused on the strategic level of the war. This is not one of those films. The Battle of Hill 66 tells the story of a small tactical level fight for a nondescript hill, in the normally placid Italian countryside. This engagement was but a small piece in the much larger Operation Diadem taking place in the early part of May 1944, the ultimate prize of which was, potentially, the eternal city, Rome.  aClosed captions in English.  aDescription based on online resource; title from title screen (Army, viewed Apr. 23, 2026). 0aWorld War, 1939-1945.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85148273 7aHistorical films.2lcgft0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf2011026311 7aInternet videos.2lcgft0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf20110263371 aParker, Roy C.,edirector.1 aMasten, Randy,efilm producer.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no20210119031https://id.oclc.org/worldcat/entity/E39PCjC9PcTjk44GkwbpDwhfv32 aArmy University Films (U.S.),eissuing body.40uhttps://purl.fdlp.gov/GPO/gpo255227704 zAddress at time of PURL creationuhttps://www.armyupress.army.mil/Films/Feature-Film-Catalog/Hill66/  aC0bGPO  abc109 20260423b20260423  aUNREPORTEDPUBSASKGPOb2026042302012nam a22003853a 00147154820260428094058.0m     o  d f      cr |||||||||||260423s2014    ohua    o    f000 0 eng d  a(OCoLC)1586921426  aGPObengelocal/GPOepncGPO  aXZL4  a0449-F-25 (online)0 aHE 20.7114/2-2:SK 3/2-MERCAPTO.00aNIOSH skin notation profiles: 2-mercaptobenzothiazole, sodium 2-mercaptobenzothiazole, zinc 2-mercaptobenzothiazole. 1aCincinnati, OH :bDepartment of Health and Human Services, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, National Insti