sitory Library Program (FDLP).  aEditor Sarah Carlsen ; Producer Randy G. Masten0 aJames Dubik, Zachary Griffiths, Heidi Urben, Emily Lopez, Lamanda Jackson, Ryan Crayne, Robert Rose, Marcel Blood, Sarah Chamberlin  aThe Harding Project is a Chief of Staff of the Army initiative to promote professional writing, foster professional development, renew branch journals, and advance military education. This film explores the project's goals and features exclusive interviews with key leaders: Harding Project Director LTC Zachary Griffiths, Deputy Director SFC Marcel Blood, LTG (Ret.) James M. Dubik, and Dubik Fellowship Senior Advisor COL (Ret.) Heidi Urben, PhD. Hear directly from Harding and Dubik Fellows about their contributions to shaping the future of the Army.  aClosed captions in English.  aDescription based on online resource; title from title screen (Army, viewed Apr. 23, 2026). 0aMilitary educationzUnited States.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85085193 7aMilitary films.2lcgft0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf2011026395 7aInternet videos.2lcgft0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf20110263371 aHasik, Hayley,edirector.2 aArmy University Films (U.S.),eissuing body.40uhttps://purl.fdlp.gov/GPO/gpo255232704 zAddress at time of PURL creationuhttps://www.armyupress.army.mil/Films/Feature-Film-Catalog/Harding-Project/  aC0bGPO  abc109 20260423b20260423  aUNREPORTEDPUBSASKGPOb2026042302429ngm a22004333i 00147155320260423105159.0m     o  d f      260423s2024    ksu015       fo   vleng d  a(OCoLC)1586921970  aGPObengerdaepncGPO  aengpeng  an-us---  aXZL4  a0359-C-11 (online)0 aD 110.2:SO 404aThe soldier and the Constitution. 1aFort Leavenworth, KS :bArmy University Films,c2024.  a1 online resource (1 video file (14 min., 28 sec.)) :bsound, color  atwo-dimensional moving imagebtdi2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  a"Published on: September 17, 2024."  aThis is a publication issued by the United States federal government or produced with federal funds.  aIn scope of the U.S. Government Publishing Office Cataloging and Indexing Program (C&I) and Federal Depository Library Program (FDLP).  aWritten by: Dave Richardson and Heidi Urben ; Director: Kimball Johnson, Randy G. Masten0 aNarrators: Sara Carlsen, Roy Parker  aThe principle of civilian control of the armed forces and the military's norm of nonpartisanship are bedrock features of democratic governance. While military service members are encouraged to exercise their basic rights as citizens, such as voting, those on active duty face a number of restrictions regarding their political activity. This film helps educate service members on the military's norm of nonpartisanship and why it's critical for the military to avoid the appearance of participating in partisan politics, especially during an election year.  aClosed captions in English.  aDescription based on online resource; title from title screen (Army, viewed Apr. 23, 2026). 0aSoldiersxPolitical activityzUnited States. 7aMilitary films.2lcgft 7aInternet videos.2lcgft2 aArmy University Films (U.S.),eissuing body.40uhttps://purl.fdlp.gov/GPO/gpo255235704 zAddress at time of PURL creationuhttps://www.armyupress.army.mil/Films/Feature-Film-Catalog/Soldier-and-the-Constitution/  aC0bGPO  abc109 20260423b20260423  aUNREPORTEDPUBSASKGPOb2026042301951nam a2200445 i 00147155420260423110411.0m     o  d f      cr |||||||||||260423e202604  ohua    obt  f000 0 eng d  a(OCoLC)1586922165  aGPObengerdaepncGPO  aXZL4  a0830-H-15 (online)0 aNAS 1.60:202600010081 aVailonis, Kristina M.,eauthor.10aPulsed electroacoustic analysis capabilities at NASA Glenn Research Center /cKristina M. Vailonis and Theresa Benyo.3 aPulsed electroacoustic analysis capabilities at National Aeronautics and Space Administration Glenn Research Center 1