epncGPO0 aengpeng  an-us-nyan-us-co  aXZL4  a0359-C-11 (online)0 aD 110.2:G 9104aThe high ground - the legacy of the 10th Mountain Division /cArmy University Films presents ; a 29 Pixel Studios production ; directed by Chris Carey.  aUnited States2naf 1aFort Leavenworth, KS :bArmy University Press,c2025.  a1 online resource (1 streaming video file (1 hr., 23 min., 36 sec.)) :bsound, color  atwo-dimensional moving imagebtdi2rdacontent  avideobv2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier0 aauditorybclosedcaptions2sapdv  adigital2rdatr  avideo file2rdaft  a"Premiered: May 09, 2025"--Army University Press website.  aThis is a publication issued by the United States federal government or produced with federal funds.  aIn scope of the U.S. Government Publishing Office Cataloging and Indexing Program (C&I) and Federal Depository Library Program (FDLP).  aProduced by Randy G. Masten, PhD, Chris Carey, PhD ; executive producers, LTG Milford Beagle, Jr., BG David Foley, COL Todd Schmidt, PhD, LTC Marc Cleveland, Don Wright, PhD ; lead editor, Sara Carlsen ; associate producer, Sara Carlsen ; camera operators, Sara Carlsen, Nick Schale ; assistant editor, Andrew Cornwell ; unit production manager, Nick Schale ; archival research, sound editor, title design, and 3D animation, Sara Carlsen.0 aFeaturing: LTC Marc Cleveland, 1SG Daniel Fields, PFC Rylan Parsons, Leah Cleveland.  a"Filmed in frigid upstate New York at Fort Drum and the majestic Colorado Rockies near Camp Hale, The High Ground follows soldiers of the 10th Mountain Division (LI) as they attempt to reconnect with their alpine roots by completing a mountain marathon eighty years in the making. The film features footage of Army soldiers skiing, snowshoeing, climbing, rappelling, and glissading during 10th Mountain Division events including the D-Series, the Hale to Vail Traverse, and Legacy Days. Army University Films and the 10th MD partnered with the Denver Public Library Special Collections and Archives, History Colorado, the National Ski Patrol (NSP), Vail Resorts, the National Outdoor Leadership School (NOLS), 10th Special Forces Group (Airborne), and the Colorado Army National Guard to create this documentary"--Army University Press website.1 aClosed captioning available in English  aDescription based on online resource; title from landing page (AUP, viewed April 21, 2026).10aUnited States.bArmy.bMountain Division, 10thxHistory. 0aSoldiersxTraining ofzColoradozCamp Hale. 0aSoldiersxTraining ofzNew York (State)zFort Drum. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zUnited StatesxMountain warfare. 7aMilitary films.2lcgft 7aDocumentary films.2lcgft 7aNonfiction films.2lcgft 7aInternet videos.2lcgft 7aVideo recordings.2lcgft1 aCarey, Christopherc(Historian),efilm director.1 aMasten, Randy,efilm producer.1https://id.oclc.org/worldcat/entity/E39PCjC9PcTjk44GkwbpDwhfv32 aArmy University Press (U.S.),eissuing body.40uhttps://purl.fdlp.gov/GPO/gpo255177704 zAddress at time of PURL creationuhttps://www.armyupress.army.mil/Films/Feature-Film-Catalog/The-High-Ground/  aC0bGPO  abc108 20260430b20260430  aBIBCONEWb20260430  aUNREPORTEDPUBSASKGPOb2026043001909ngm a22004573i 00147196020260430145024.0m     o  c f      cr cna||||||||vz czazz|260430s2024    dcu006       fo   vleng d  a(OCoLC)1587455649  aGPObengerdaepncGPO0 aengpeng  an-us---  aXZL4  a0306 (online)0 aD 1.2:M 59/2500aForeign military sales 101. 1a[Washington, D.C.] :bDefense Security Cooperation Agency,c2024.  a1 online resource (1 streaming video file (5 min., 18 sec.)) :bsound, color  atwo-dimensional moving imagebtdi2rdacontent  avideobv2rdamedia  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier0 aauditorybclosedCaptions2sapdv  avideo file2rdaft  aThis is a publication issued by the United States federal government or produced with 