nd C).1 aNOAA weather charts (series A, B, and C)1 aNational Centers for Environmental Prediction weather analyses and forecasts charts 1a[Asheville, N.C.] :bNational Centers for Environmental Information  a1 online resource  aUpdated daily  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  a"The Weather Analyses and Forecasts Charts from the NOAA National Weather Service (NWS) National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) are produced on a daily basis at meteorological synoptic times, normally at 00 and 12 UTC. Chart contents contain constant pressure charts, including the analyses and forecasts of heights, temperatures, winds, relative humidity, vertical velocity, vorticity, lifted index, thickness levels, and wind shear. Also available are surface analyses and charts of the Atlantic and Pacific with special emphasis on specific areas such as the Gulf of Alaska. The geographic coverage of includes the Northern and Southern Hemispheres, Tropical and Polar Regions. The charts are represented in 6-bit binary, TIFF, JPEG and GIF image file formats over the period of record from February 1994 to the present."  aThis is a publication issued by the United States federal government or produced with federal funds.  aIn scope of the U.S. Government Publishing Office Cataloging and Indexing Program (C&I) and Federal Depository Library Program (FDLP).0 aContents viewed Apr. 30, 2026 (NCEI); title from homepage caption. 0aClimatologyxObservationsvCharts, diagrams, etc. 0aUpper atmospherexObservationsvCharts, diagrams, etc. 0aPrecipitation (Meteorology)xObservationsvCharts, diagrams, etc. 0aWeather forecastingxObservationsvCharts, diagrams, etc. 7aMeteorological charts.2lcgft2 aNational Centers for Environmental Prediction (U.S.),eissuing body.2 aNational Centers for Environmental Information (U.S.),eissuing body.0 tNOAA weather chartsw(DLC) 97644533w(OCoLC)3574534840uhttps://purl.fdl